org.persona.ontology
Class ManagedIndividual

java.lang.Object
  org.persona.middleware.PResource
      org.persona.ontology.ManagedIndividual
Direct Known Subclasses:
AccessImpairment, ComparableIndividual, ContextProvider, ContextProviderType, DialogType, DimensionMeasure, Gender, Modality, MultiDimensionMeasure, Service, SetTopBox
public abstract class ManagedIndividual
extends PResource

The root of the whole manageable class hierarchy in PERSONA.

Conventions to be followed by all subclasses in the class hierarchy rooted at ManagedIndividual are:

  1. They must define a public static final field of type String with the name MY_URI initialized by the URI of the ontology class they represent.
  2. They must register to the PERSONA ontology in a static code segment using the protected static method register(Class) below.
  3. all the public and static methods provided by the ancestors in the class hierarchy that are not declared as final should be overridden; in case of the direct subclasses of ManagedIndividual, they must overwrite getRDFSComment(), getRDFSLabel(), getClassRestrictionsOnProperty(String), and getStandardPropertyURIs(), and may overwrite getEnumerationMembers() and getIndividualByURI(String).
    4. The latter two may be left out, if the default implementations by this class (which always returns null) apply. All subclasses that enumerate their members must overwrite them anyhow.
  4. Instance methods that are serious candidates to be overwritten are PResource.isClosedCollection(String) and setProperty(String, Object). Please read the comments below on these methods as well as comments provided within PResource.

Author:
mtazari

getPropSerializationType

public abstract int getPropSerializationType(String propURI)
Answers if the given property has to be considered when serializing this individual in a minimized way, and if not ignore-able, whether its value should be presented in its full form or can be reduced. The return value must be one of PResource.PROP_SERIALIZATION_OPTIONAL, PResource.PROP_SERIALIZATION_REDUCED, or PResource.PROP_SERIALIZATION_FULL. It can be assumed that the given property is one of those returned by PResource.getPropertyURIs(). Decision criterion should be if the value of this property is absolutely necessary when this resource is being sent to a remote node. If the subclass rates it as unlikely that the receiver side would need this info, the answer should be PROP_SERIALIZATION_OPTIONAL in favor of lower communication traffic and higher performance even at risk of a possible additional query on the receiver side for fetching this info. With the same rationale, if a property should be included in the process of serialization, it is preferable to include it in a reduced form; in this case the return value should be PROP_SERIALIZATION_REDUCED, otherwise PROP_SERIALIZATION_FULL can be returned.

Overrides:
getPropSerializationType in class PResource
